RANCHLAND SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Ranchland Solar, LLC (Ranchland Solar) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (Reactive Supply Service) from the Ranchland Solar generating facility (Ranchland Solar Facility).
The Ranchland Solar Facility is a solar generating facility located in Currituck County, North Carolina. The Ranchland Solar Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Virginia Electric and Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (PJM).
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Ranchland Solars revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Ranchland Solar Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Ranchland Solars monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Ranchland Solar shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJMs Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $589,883.89. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $49,156.99.
